WorkItem.ClosedComment: This is an internal implementation detail for the compiler.
WorkItem.Description:
I'm using IHashTable (well, really StringHashTable) from the compiler's implementation but sometimes I need to delete key-data pairs from my table.  Right now I'm just doing "addOrUpdate" with the key the key I want removed and data is undefined, but this seems rather hacky.  I could write my own hashtable with all of the features fairly easily, but I feel like it's better to use the "official" one since having an official hash table seems like a good idea.  Is there a better way to do this, or a more official hashtable?

EDIT: Thanks MgSam for helping me clarify that I'm using the compiler's implementation.

Comments.Message: The "Issues" section of CodePlex is for bugs or feature requests. You should post a question like this on [Stack Overflow](stackoverflow.com) with the tag "TypeScript". You also will need to include your code so people will know what you're referring to.
Update (since there's no edit button!): Ah ok, sorry, I see you're referencing the compiler's implementation of IHashTable. You should make your post a little more clear about that at least.
